fields.name: Karumba Kinyua
fields.title: Managing Partner
fields.profile:
Karumba is a professional with over 19 years practical experience focusing on Monitoring and Evaluation, financial and risk management, business development and strategic management.
He has a Master of Science in Corporate Real Estate Finance & Strategy and a Bachelor of Commerce (Business Administration). He has extensive experience with international and regional institutions in sub-Saharan Africa, Europe and North America.
He has worked for government agencies, financial institutions, agribusiness firms, faith-based institutions and investments companies.

fields.name: Kathrine Njuguna
fields.title: Investment Analyst
fields.profile:
Kathrine works as an Investment Analyst handling financial models, investment memos, strategic plans, research and supports the team in execution of mandates. She works closely with clients engaging them through different phases of their business cycle from ideation, start-up, commercialization, growth, restructuring and development.
She has handled a variety of clients in different sectors including agribusiness, finance, health, food and beverage, manufacturing, training and consultancy. She holds a Bachelor’s degree in Economics and Finance from Kenyatta University and is currently a CFA Level 2 Exam Candidate.

fields.name: Everlyne Ombasa
fields.title: Research Analyst
fields.profile: Everlyne is a flexible and ambitious individual with an industrious work ethic. Looking to make impactful contributions in the field of research and data analysis that will yield informative and innovative solutions to the corporate business industry. Pursues to positively touch individuals and communities by providing comprehensive and accurate data on social and economic topics that will result in life-changing engagements for the local communities. She is experienced in applied research and data management, able to manipulate large complex data sets using a variety of applications (SPSS, STATA, Excel, Microsoft Office suite). Holds a Bachelor of Arts degree in Economics.

fields.name: Karen Wachira
fields.title: Risk Analyst
fields.profile: Karen is a Risk Analyst with experience in finance, actuarial analysis, Investment Analysis, Risk Analysis, Financial modelling and Business Continuity Planning. She holds a Bachelor Science in Actuarial Science from Jomo Kenyatta University of Agriculture and Technology and has passed the CFA Exam Level 1.

fields.name: Timothy Madegwa
fields.title: Risk And ICT Consultant
fields.profile: Timothy holds a Bachelor of Science in Mathematics and Computer Science from the Jomo Kenyatta University of Agriculture and Technology. He is equipped with many skills which include Enterprise Risk Management, Web Development, Machine Learning, Data Analytics and Data Science. He has great passion in bring Risk Management and ICT together to build smart systems that make work easier.

fields.name: Dr. Fredrick Ogolla
fields.title: Associate Consultant
fields.profile: Dr. Fredrick is a Strategy formulation, Strategy Execution and Change Management Professional. He holds PhD in Management Science and Innovation with a focus on Strategy and Execution from ESADE Business School Barcelona Spain. He has been involved in developing 677 strategic Plans.

fields.name: Gideon Mureithi
fields.title: Associate Consultant
fields.profile: Gideon is a Research and Strategy expert. He has over ten years’ experience in research, strategy and management. His top 5 strengths are: Accountability, Vision, Ideation, Strategic and Objectivity.

fields.name: Isaac Kimathi
fields.title: Associate Consultant
fields.profile: Isaac is a Research and Strategic Planning Expert. He is experienced in conducting National Marketing surveys and Baseline studies. He is well informed on Data quality management and analysis using SPSS, CSPro, EpiData and R.

fields.name: Njenga Kinyanjui
fields.title: Associate Consultant
fields.profile: Njenga is a Human Resource Expert. He is competent in Executive Search and Selection/Head-hunting, Technical Recruiting, High Volume Recruiting, Advanced Boolean Search, Candidate Sourcing, Talent Pool Diversity, Resume Screening, Competency – based Interviewing, Offer Negotiation and Onboarding, and Reference Checks.

fields.requirements:
Ultimately the responsibility is to increase the speed and efficiency of common data team workflows. Below are some examples of how you may achieve this
Improve the overall Data team’s workflow through knowledge sharing, proper documentation, and code review
Deliver/review new automation frameworks within the team
Work on efficient ingestion of new data into our data warehouse using tools such as Python, Spark, Airflow, ADF, Databricks, Azure Data Lake, etc
Work on efficient storage of our data in the data warehouse, identifying performance improvements from query to table redesign.
Work on the careful design of the schema’s, table names, data models, and practices within the data warehouse, creating a well-curated data set.
Rewrite our data model using dbt or similar, and empower other analysts to use the frameworks, developing their skills with mentoring and good code review.
Identify re-usable elements of downstream analytics and move into the repeatable data model Contribute to our internal python and R libraries, driving best practice

fields.title: Why we should all invest
fields.paragraph_1: "But I must explain to you how all this mistaken idea of denouncing pleasure and praising pain was born and I will give you a complete account of the system, and expound the actual teachings of the great explorer of the truth, the master-builder of human happiness. No one rejects, dislikes, or avoids pleasure itself, because it is pleasure, but because those who do not know how to pursue pleasure rationally encounter consequences that are extremely painful. Nor again is there anyone who loves or pursues or desires to obtain pain of itself, because it is pain, but because occasionally circumstances occur in which toil and pain can procure him some great pleasure. To take a trivial example, which of us ever undertakes laborious physical exercise, except to obtain some advantage from it? But who has any right to find fault with a man who chooses to enjoy a pleasure that has no annoying consequences, or one who avoids a pain that produces no resultant pleasure?"
fields.paragraph_2: On the other hand, we denounce with righteous indignation and dislike men who are so beguiled and demoralized by the charms of pleasure of the moment, so blinded by desire, that they cannot foresee the pain and trouble that are bound to ensue; and equal blame belongs to those who fail in their duty through weakness of will, which is the same as saying through shrinking from toil and pain. These cases are perfectly simple and easy to distinguish. In a free hour, when our power of choice is untrammelled and when nothing prevents our being able to do what we like best, every pleasure is to be welcomed and every pain avoided. But in certain circumstances and owing to the claims of duty or the obligations of business it will frequently occur that pleasures have to be repudiated and annoyances accepted. The wise man therefore always holds in these matters to this principle of selection: he rejects pleasures to secure other greater pleasures, or else he endures pains to avoid worse pains.
